{
  "doc_id": "28729",
  "text": "The implemented GA uses a trimmed down variant of the Kernighan-Lin [CITATION_1] optimization algorithm. The traditional Kernighan-Lin heuristic has a time complexity of O(n 3 ) and is not guaranteed to provide the minimum bisection. The algorithm's time complexity is trimmed down in the exact way that is described in Bui and Moon's paper on graph partitioning with a GA [CITATION_2] .",
